      "analysis_type_plural": "intellectual genealogies",
      "core_question": "Where do these ideas come from, how did they travel, and what got lost or transformed along the way?",
      "extraction_steps": [
        "IDENTIFY KEY THINKERS: Who are the intellectual figures referenced? What are their key contributions? What traditions do they belong to?",
        "MAP TRADITIONS: What intellectual traditions are at play? What are their core commitments? Who are their canonical figures?",
        "TRACE UNIT IDEAS (Lovejoy): What persistent ideas travel across thinkers and periods? How do they transform?",
        "TRACE CONCEPT GENEALOGIES: How did specific concepts evolve? What did they mean at different stages?",
        "MAP INFLUENCES: Who influenced whom? What was transmitted? What was transformed? What was rejected?",
        "FIND CREATIVE MISREADINGS (Bloom): Where did productive misreadings occur? How did 'getting it wrong' produce something new?",
        "TRACE INTELLECTUAL DEBTS: What do thinkers owe to predecessors? Is it acknowledged?",
        "BUILD TRANSMISSION PATHS: How did ideas travel from thinker to thinker? What happened along the way?",
        "MAP INTELLECTUAL CONFLICTS: What debates shaped the field? Who fought? Over what? Who won?",
        "DO GENEALOGICAL ANALYSIS (Foucault): What accidents, struggles, and power plays produced what now seems natural?",
        "IDENTIFY CANONICAL TEXTS: What works are treated as foundational? How are they received?",
        "MAP INSTITUTIONAL CONTEXTS: What universities, journals, schools shaped intellectual production?",
        "BUILD THE RELATIONSHIP GRAPH: Connect all figures, traditions, concepts, texts"
      ],
      "key_fields": {
        "thinker_id": "Individual intellectual figures",
        "tradition_id": "Schools of thought",
        "influence_id": "How ideas traveled between thinkers",
        "misreading_id": "Creative transformations through 'misunderstanding'"
